span class=\"s2\">Yusef Omowale, <a href=\"mailto:omowale@socallib.org\"><span class=\"s3\">omowale@socallib.org</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s2\">Michele Welsing, <a href=\"mailto:mwelsing@socallib.org\"><span class=\"s3\">mwelsing@socallib.org</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p5\"><span class=\"s4\"><b>Board</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p6\"><span class=\"s4\">Naomi Boas, Treasurer; former Community Technology Director, Little Tokyo Service Center</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p6\"><span class=\"s4\">Susan Burton, Secretary; Executive Director, A New Way of Life Re-Entry Project</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p6\"><span class=\"s4\">Yusef Omowale, Library Director</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p6\"><span class=\"s4\">Damien Sojoyner, President; Professor of Africana Studies, Scripps College</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p6\"><span class=\"s4\"><i>Professional affiliations of board members are listed for identification purposes only.</i></span></p>','Who runs SCL?','','publish','closed','closed','','who-runs-scl','','','2018-04-20 02:57:10','2018-04-20 09:57:10','',0,'https://operationscl.000webhostapp.com/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=448',0,'ufaq','',0),(449,5,'2018-04-20 02:59:47','2018-04-20 09:59:47','<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The Library is generally available for research Wednesday through Saturday from 11:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m. (last appointment at 4:00 p.m.). The Library is closed on Sundays and Mondays.</span></p>','When is SCL opened?','','publish','closed','closed','','when-is-scl-opened','','','2018-04-20 02:59:47','2018-04-20 09:59:47','',0,'https://operationscl.000webhostapp.com/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=449',0,'ufaq','',0),(450,5,'2018-04-20 03:00:55','2018-04-20 10:00:55','<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">If you are planning a research visit to the Library, we ask that you fill out the <a href=\"http://www.socallib.org/research/appointments\"><span class=\"s2\">Research Request Form</span></a> to make an appointment. This will help ensure that the Library is open on the date you plan to visit, and a staff member will be available to assist you.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s3\">Upon arrival at the front desk, you will be asked to sign in before beginning research. Library staff will retrieve requested materials from our closed stacks. We ask that you follow certain guidelines while using the collections:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"ul1\">\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">Food and drink are not allowed in proximity to archival collections. You may bring food and drink and store it in the Library’s refrigerator and consume it in areas away from archival material.</span></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">To view documents, simply complete a request slip, which we will provide, and present it to staff. We will bring your items to you.</span></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">Records may be used only at the research tables.</span></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">Researchers may use up to three boxes at a time. Records must be left in the order in which they are found.</span></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">If you would like to make photocopies or scan or take photos of materials, we will provide paper tags you can use to mark document locations; do not remove the documents from their folders.</span></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">Please note that we are not always a \"quiet\" library. There may be community events or other programming going on during your visit so you may want to bring along headphones.</span></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">The Library staff will give a last call 30 minutes before closing. We will not retrieve documents after that time.</span></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">When possible, please consider providing the Library with a courtesy copy of publications or products made possible by research in our holdings.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s3\">Upon arrival at the front desk, you will be asked to sign in before beginning research. Library staff will retrieve requested materials from our closed stacks. We ask that you follow certain guidelines while using the collections:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"ul1\">\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">Food and drink are not allowed in proximity to archival collections. You may bring food and drink and store it in the Library’s refrigerator and consume it in areas away from archival material.</span></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">To view documents, simply complete a request slip, which we will provide, and present it to staff. We will bring your items to you.</span></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">Records may be used only at the research tables.</span></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">Researchers may use up to three boxes at a time. Records must be left in the order in which they are found.</span></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">If you would like to make photocopies or scan or take photos of materials, we will provide paper tags you can use to mark document locations; do not remove the documents from their folders.</span></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">Please note that we are not always a \"quiet\" library. There may be community events or other programming going on during your visit so you may want to bring along headphones.</span></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">The Library staff will give a last call 30 minutes before closing. We will not retrieve documents after that time.</span></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"li4\"><span class=\"s3\">When possible, please consider providing the Library with a courtesy copy of publications or products made possible by research in our holdings.</span></li>\r\n</ul>','I want to visit SCL. How do I prepare for a visit?','','publish','closed','closed','','i-want-to-visit-scl-how-do-i-prepare-for-a-visit','','','2018-04-20 03:00:55','2018-04-20 10:00:55','',0,'https://operationscl.000webhostapp.com/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=450',0,'ufaq','',0),(451,5,'2018-04-20 03:04:16','2018-04-20 10:04:16','<div class=\"ewd-ufaq-shortcode-help\">[select-faq faq_id=\'447\']</div>\r\n<div class=\"ewd-ufaq-shortcode-help\">[select-faq faq_id=\'450\']</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"ewd-ufaq-shortcode-help\">[select-faq faq_id=\'449\']</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"ewd-ufaq-shortcode-help\">[select-faq faq_id=\'448\']</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"ewd-ufaq-shortcode-help\"></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;','FAQ','','publish','closed','closed','','faq','','','2018-04-27 00:05:14','2018-04-27 07:05:14','',0,'https://operationscl.000webhostapp.com/?page_id=451',0,'page','',0),(452,5,'2018-04-20 03:04:16','2018-04-20 10:04:16','[ultimate-faqs]','FAQ','','inherit','closed','closed','','451-revision-v1','','','2018-04-20 03:04:16','2018-04-20 10:04:16','',451,'https://operationscl.000webhostapp.com/2018/04/451-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(454,5,'2018-04-20 03:05:17','2018-04-20 10:05:17',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','454','','','2018-04-20 03:05:17','2018-04-20 10:05:17','',0,'https://operationscl.000webhostapp.com/?p=454',10,'nav_menu_item','',0),(455,1,'2018-04-20 15:48:15','2018-04-20 22:48:15','{\n    \"square-child::square_social_twitter\": {\n        \"value\": \"\",\n        \"type\": \"theme_mod\",\n        \"user_id\": 1,\n        \"date_modified_gmt\": \"2018-04-20 22:47:36\"\n    },\n    \"square-child::square_social_instagram\": {\n        \"value\": \"\",\n        \"type\": \"theme_mod\",\n        \"user_id\": 1,\n        \"date_modified_gmt\": \"2018-04-20 22:47:36\"\n    },\n    \"square-child::square_social_facebook\": {\n        \"value\": \"https://www.facebook.com/socallib/\",\n        \"type\": \"theme_mod\",\n        \"user_id\": 1,\n        \"date_modified_gmt\": \"2018-04-20 22:48:15\"\n    }\n}','','','trash','closed','closed','','8d2928ca-e3f1-493c-a70